description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join a vibrant and busy NHS ICT Service Desk, based in Leamington Spa.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Service Desk offers a high-quality customer focused helpline to all South Warwickshire NHS Foundation Trust and GP Practice staff based in sites across Warwickshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be an enthusiastic person with a flexible attitude, able to work well as a team player. With exceptional communication skills both verbal and written; you will work well with others and have the drive and passion for working in a constantly evolving and demanding environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your experience of working in a customer focussed service delivery&lt;em&gt;, &lt;/em&gt;call centre or helpdesk environment means you are able to plan and organise a variety of tasks with differing priorities; have an analytical approach to problem solving; have fast and accurate keyboard skills; have a working knowledge of the Microsoft Office Suite; and be confident to learn new skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Having excellent IT skills will be key, as will being a dynamic and creative individual that take prides in delivering a first-class customer service, providing prompt action that ensuring the user receives a positive experience whilst addressing their needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held via MS Teams during the week commencing 16th November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name - Avinder Channa - Job title - Technical Services Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email addressAvinder.channa@swft.nhs.ukTelephone number01926 495321 x 6534&lt;/p&gt;
